<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-04-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-04-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="100" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Secretary’s Daily Meetings, lot 58 D
                            609</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Executive
                                Secretary (<persName corresp="#p_MWJ1">McWilliams</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date" when="1952-04-25">April 25,
                                    1952</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>Subject:</head>
                            <item>Summary of Meeting with the Secretary.</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="participants">
                            <head>Participants:</head>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">Acheson</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">Bruce</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_SHH1">Sargeant</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MJK1">McFall</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_JPC1">Jessup</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1">Howe</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Nitze</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MWJ1">McWilliams</persName></item>
                            <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BLD1">Battle</persName></item>
                        </list>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Item 1. <hi rend="italic">Korean Briefing</hi></p>
                        <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HF1">Howe</persName> gave the briefing.</p>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Item 2. <hi rend="italic">Negotiations in Korea</hi></p>
                        <p>Practically the entire meeting was spent in a discussion of the current
                            state of negotiations in Korea and the steps which should be taken to
                            prepare American and world opinion for the decisive turn of events which
                            seems to be at hand. The two main questions at issue are: <list>
                                <label>(1)</label>
                                <item>Should we make a public statement in respect to the build-up
                                    of Communist strength and the probability of a heavy resumption
                                    of hostilities. General <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> is anxious that something be done on
                                    this.</item>
                                <label>(2)</label>
                                <item>Should we have congressional consultations at this stage of
                                    the negotiations.</item>
                            </list></p>
                        <pb facs="0205" n="171" xml:id="pg_171"/>
                        <p>The matter was left that Messrs. <persName corresp="#p_MHF1">Matthews</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SHH1">Sargeant</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BCE1">Bohlen</persName>,
                                <persName corresp="#p_MJK1">McFall</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName> would get together this morning
                            and try to outline the course of action which should be taken during the
                            next 48 hours.</p>
                        <p>[Here follows a summary of discussions on Trieste and the Varvaressos
                            report on Greece. For documentation on these two issues, see <ref target="frus1952-54v08">volume VIII</ref>.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MWJ1"><hi rend="smallcaps">W. J.
                                        McWilliams</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>